---
import TacticalHeading from '../TacticalHeading.astro';
---

<section class="crypto-primitives" id="crypto" aria-labelledby="crypto-heading">
  <div class="crypto-primitives__container">
    <TacticalHeading
      badge="CRYPTOGRAPHIC PRIMITIVES"
      title="Encryption Deep Dive"
      subtitle="Every algorithm chosen for a documented reason. No obscure crypto. No roll-your-own primitives."
    />

    <div class="crypto-cards">

      <!-- Card 1: PBKDF2 -->
      <article class="crypto-card crypto-card--derivation">
        <div class="crypto-card__header">
          <span class="crypto-badge crypto-badge--derivation">KEY DERIVATION</span>
          <h3 class="crypto-card__headline">PBKDF2-HMAC-SHA256</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="crypto-card__big-number" aria-label="600,000 iterations">
          600,000
        </div>

        <p class="crypto-card__body">
          Password-Based Key Derivation Function 2. Transforms your master password into a 256-bit
          cryptographic key by running it through HMAC-SHA256 in a tight loop &mdash; 600,000 times.
          Each iteration depends on the last. You cannot skip iterations. There is no shortcut.
        </p>

        <div class="crypto-info-box">
          <div class="crypto-info-box__header">
            <svg class="crypto-info-box__icon" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
              <circle cx="8" cy="8" r="7" stroke="#8B9A46" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <path d="M8 7v4M8 5h.01" stroke="#8B9A46" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            </svg>
            <span class="crypto-info-box__title">WHY 600,000 ITERATIONS?</span>
          </div>
          <p class="crypto-info-box__text">
            OWASP 2023 recommends a minimum of 600,000 iterations for PBKDF2-HMAC-SHA256. This reflects
            the current cost of GPU-based brute-force attacks. At 600k iterations on modern hardware, a
            single password trial takes approximately 0.3&ndash;0.8 seconds. An attacker testing 1 billion
            passwords would need over 9 years on a single GPU.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="crypto-code">
          <div class="crypto-code__bar">
            <span class="crypto-code__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="crypto-code__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="crypto-code__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="crypto-code__lang">python</span>
          </div>
          <pre class="crypto-code__block"><code><span class="code-var">key</span> <span class="code-op">=</span> <span class="code-fn">PBKDF2HMAC</span>(
    <span class="code-param">algorithm</span><span class="code-op">=</span>hashes.<span class="code-fn">SHA256</span>(),
    <span class="code-param">length</span><span class="code-op">=</span><span class="code-num">32</span>,
    <span class="code-param">salt</span><span class="code-op">=</span>salt,
    <span class="code-param">iterations</span><span class="code-op">=</span><span class="code-num">600_000</span>,
).<span class="code-fn">derive</span>(master_password.<span class="code-fn">encode</span>())</code></pre>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- Card 2: Fernet -->
      <article class="crypto-card crypto-card--encryption">
        <div class="crypto-card__header">
          <span class="crypto-badge crypto-badge--encryption">SYMMETRIC ENCRYPTION</span>
          <h3 class="crypto-card__headline">Fernet &mdash; AES-256-CBC + HMAC-SHA256</h3>
        </div>

        <p class="crypto-card__body">
          Fernet provides authenticated encryption. An attacker who modifies ciphertext cannot decrypt
          it &mdash; the HMAC will fail first. This prevents tampering, padding oracle attacks, and
          bitflip attacks simultaneously.
        </p>

        <div class="crypto-props-grid">
          <div class="crypto-prop">
            <span class="crypto-prop__label">Algorithm</span>
            <span class="crypto-prop__value">AES-256-CBC</span>
          </div>
          <div class="crypto-prop">
            <span class="crypto-prop__label">Authentication</span>
            <span class="crypto-prop__value">HMAC-SHA256</span>
          </div>
          <div class="crypto-prop">
            <span class="crypto-prop__label">Key size</span>
            <span class="crypto-prop__value">256 bits</span>
          </div>
          <div class="crypto-prop">
            <span class="crypto-prop__label">IV</span>
            <span class="crypto-prop__value">Random 128-bit per op</span>
          </div>
          <div class="crypto-prop">
            <span class="crypto-prop__label">Format</span>
            <span class="crypto-prop__value">Self-describing token</span>
          </div>
          <div class="crypto-prop">
            <span class="crypto-prop__label">Tamper detection</span>
            <span class="crypto-prop__value crypto-prop__value--yes">Yes &mdash; always</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- Card 3: System Key -->
      <article class="crypto-card crypto-card--binding">
        <div class="crypto-card__header">
          <span class="crypto-badge crypto-badge--binding">HARDWARE BINDING</span>
          <h3 class="crypto-card__headline">System Key &mdash; Machine-Specific Second Layer</h3>
        </div>

        <p class="crypto-card__body">
          The vault is encrypted twice. The derived key (from your password) is one layer. The system
          key is the second &mdash; derived from hardware identifiers unique to your machine.
        </p>

        <div class="crypto-code">
          <div class="crypto-code__bar">
            <span class="crypto-code__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="crypto-code__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="crypto-code__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="crypto-code__lang">python</span>
          </div>
          <pre class="crypto-code__block"><code><span class="code-var">hardware_id</span> <span class="code-op">=</span> <span class="code-fn">sha256</span>(cpu_serial <span class="code-op">+</span> motherboard_uuid <span class="code-op">+</span> hostname <span class="code-op">+</span> os_user)
<span class="code-var">system_key</span> <span class="code-op">=</span> <span class="code-fn">PBKDF2HMAC</span>(
    <span class="code-param">algorithm</span><span class="code-op">=</span>hashes.<span class="code-fn">SHA256</span>(),
    <span class="code-param">length</span><span class="code-op">=</span><span class="code-num">32</span>,
    <span class="code-param">salt</span><span class="code-op">=</span>hardware_salt,
    <span class="code-param">iterations</span><span class="code-op">=</span><span class="code-num">600_000</span>,
).<span class="code-fn">derive</span>(hardware_id)</code></pre>
        </div>
      </article>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  /* ============================================================
     CRYPTO PRIMITIVES SECTION
     ============================================================ */
  .crypto-primitives {
    padding: 6rem 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .crypto-primitives__container {
    max-width: 820px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* ---- Card stack ---- */
  .crypto-cards {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 4rem;
  }

  /* ---- Base card ---- */
  .crypto-card {
    background-color: #0D1208;
    border: 1px solid rgba(74, 93, 35, 0.25);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 2rem 2rem 2.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
    transition: border-color 0.25s ease;
  }

  .crypto-card:hover {
    border-color: rgba(74, 93, 35, 0.5);
  }

  /* Left border accents per card */
  .crypto-card--derivation {
    border-left: 3px solid #8B9A46;
  }

  .crypto-card--encryption {
    border-left: 3px solid #00FF41;
  }

  .crypto-card--binding {
    border-left: 3px solid #4A6B8B;
  }

  /* ---- Card header ---- */
  .crypto-card__header {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .crypto-card__headline {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #e2e8f0;
    margin: 0;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  /* ---- Badges ---- */
  .crypto-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    width: fit-content;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.65rem;
    font-family: ui-monospace, "Cascadia Code", "Fira Code", "JetBrains Mono", Menlo, Monaco, "Courier New", monospace;
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    border-radius: 2px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .crypto-badge--derivation {
    color: #0D1208;
    background-color: #8B9A46;
  }

  .crypto-badge--encryption {
    color: #0D1208;
    background-color: #00FF41;
  }

  .crypto-badge--binding {
    color: #e2e8f0;
    background-color: #4A6B8B;
  }

  /* ---- Big number ---- */
  .crypto-card__big-number {
    font-family: ui-monospace, "Cascadia Code", "Fira Code", "JetBrains Mono", Menlo, Monaco, "Courier New", monospace;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 3.75rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: #8B9A46;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1;
    text-shadow: 0 0 30px rgba(139, 154, 70, 0.4), 0 0 60px rgba(139, 154, 70, 0.15);
  }

  /* ---- Body text ---- */
  .crypto-card__body {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #78909C;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ---- Info box ---- */
  .crypto-info-box {
    background-color: rgba(139, 154, 70, 0.06);
    border: 1px solid rgba(139, 154, 70, 0.18);
    border-radius: 3px;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .crypto-info-box__header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.625rem;
  }

  .crypto-info-box__icon {
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .crypto-info-box__title {
    font-family: ui-monospace, "Cascadia Code", "Fira Code", "JetBrains Mono", Menlo, Monaco, "Courier New", monospace;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: #8B9A46;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .crypto-info-box__text {
    font-size: 0.825rem;
    color: #78909C;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ---- Code blocks (army terminal look) ---- */
  .crypto-code {
    background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
    border: 1px solid rgba(139, 154, 70, 0.15);
    border-radius: 3px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .crypto-code__bar {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.3rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(139, 154, 70, 0.08);
  }

  .crypto-code__dot {
    width: 7px;
    height: 7px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: rgba(139, 154, 70, 0.35);
  }

  .crypto-code__lang {
    margin-left: auto;
    font-family: ui-monospace, "Cascadia Code", "Fira Code", "JetBrains Mono", Menlo, Monaco, "Courier New", monospace;
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(139, 154, 70, 0.5);
  }

  .crypto-code__block {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    font-family: ui-monospace, "Cascadia Code", "Fira Code", "JetBrains Mono", Menlo, Monaco, "Courier New", monospace;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: #00FF41;
    overflow-x: auto;
    tab-size: 4;
  }

  .crypto-code__block code {
    color: #00FF41;
  }

  /* Syntax highlighting tokens */
  .code-var {
    color: #e2e8f0;
  }

  .code-op {
    color: #78909C;
  }

  .code-fn {
    color: #00FF41;
  }

  .code-param {
    color: #8B9A46;
  }

  .code-num {
    color: #FFD700;
  }

  /* ---- Properties grid (3x2) ---- */
  .crypto-props-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1px;
    background-color: rgba(74, 93, 35, 0.15);
    border: 1px solid rgba(74, 93, 35, 0.15);
    border-radius: 3px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .crypto-prop {
    background-color: #0D1208;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }

  .crypto-prop__label {
    font-family: ui-monospace, "Cascadia Code", "Fira Code", "JetBrains Mono", Menlo, Monaco, "Courier New", monospace;
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #546E7A;
  }

  .crypto-prop__value {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #e2e8f0;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .crypto-prop__value--yes {
    color: #00FF41;
  }

  /* ---- Responsive ---- */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .crypto-card {
      padding: 1.5rem 1.25rem 1.75rem;
    }

    .crypto-props-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }

    .crypto-card__big-number {
      font-size: 2.25rem;
    }

    .crypto-info-box {
      padding: 1rem 1.125rem;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 420px) {
    .crypto-props-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
